. . .of a new nation.

801
01:20:11,893 --> 01:20:13,292
And do you know why. . .

802
01:20:13,533 --> 01:20:15,046
. . .it will be me?

803
01:20:19,373 --> 01:20:21,045
Because l can.

804
01:20:30,533 --> 01:20:31,761
Stop it!

805
01:20:36,053 --> 01:20:37,372
You're killing him!

806
01:20:38,013 --> 01:20:38,889
Let me go!

807
01:20:41,173 --> 01:20:42,492
Olease, let me go!

808
01:20:49,973 --> 01:20:51,884
Help him, somebody!
Olease!

809
01:21:00,173 --> 01:21:01,731
You didn't have to--!

810
01:21:02,333 --> 01:21:03,812
Didn't have to what?

811
01:21:06,813 --> 01:21:08,212
You bastard!

812
01:21:09,933 --> 01:21:11,332
You killed him!

813
01:21:12,053 --> 01:21:14,123
Your people seem seditious.

814
01:21:15,533 --> 01:21:17,489
You seem seditious.

815
01:21:18,733 --> 01:21:20,928
What am l seeing here?

816
01:21:21,373 --> 01:21:22,123
l'm waiting!

817
01:21:31,333 --> 01:21:35,121
A man came through with mail.
Said he was a postman.

818
01:21:35,373 --> 01:21:37,933
Said that the government
had been restored back east.

819
01:21:38,173 --> 01:21:39,925
What government?

820
01:21:40,493 --> 01:21:43,405
The United States government!

821
01:21:45,253 --> 01:21:46,288
Who said that?

822
01:22:03,653 --> 01:22:05,769
Which way did he go?

823
01:22:06,653 --> 01:22:08,291
Do not make me ask again.

824
01:22:08,533 --> 01:22:09,329
East.

825
01:22:10,413 --> 01:22:12,244
Send a patrol east!

826
01:22:12,893 --> 01:22:13,928
Send 3 more. . .

827
01:22:14,533 --> 01:22:15,966
. . .north, south and west!

828
01:22:17,453 --> 01:22:19,171
They'd better find him east.

829
01:22:38,533 --> 01:22:40,728
Take that damn shirt off, Johnny!

830
01:22:44,013 --> 01:22:45,685
l managed to save these.

831
01:22:45,933 --> 01:22:47,730
Do you want to die too?

832
01:22:49,533 --> 01:22:52,093
l'm headed south with the mail.

833
01:22:54,973 --> 01:22:56,531
Don't be a fool.

834
01:22:57,213 --> 01:22:58,646
What should l be?

835
01:23:10,413 --> 01:23:11,687
Rachel Clark.

836
01:23:15,053 --> 01:23:17,283
"Charlie Sykes. "

837
01:23:23,933 --> 01:23:25,366
"Graham Drewitt. "

838
01:23:26,013 --> 01:23:28,652
G.D. died of flu last winter.

839
01:23:31,133 --> 01:23:32,805
That's all there is.

840
01:23:34,493 --> 01:23:35,721
That's all there is, folks.

841
01:23:36,293 --> 01:23:37,009
For now.

842
01:23:38,333 --> 01:23:42,804
But there'll be more, lots more,
once there's a real system in place.

843
01:23:44,093 --> 01:23:45,048
Right?

844
01:23:48,853 --> 01:23:49,888
What about New York City?

845
01:23:51,533 --> 01:23:52,807
Did they survive the plague?

846
01:23:55,733 --> 01:23:56,882
Survive?

847
01:23:59,733 --> 01:24:01,963
They got Broadway up and running again.

848
01:24:05,613 --> 01:24:08,446
There's a kid doing Andrew Floyd Webber,
you wouldn't believe.

849
01:24:08,693 --> 01:24:10,285
How much is it to mail a letter?

850
01:24:11,293 --> 01:24:12,408
"Mail. . . . "

851
01:24:39,413 --> 01:24:40,687
They won't open the gates.

852
01:24:43,053 --> 01:24:46,887
They say they got a representative
of the Restored United States in there.

853
01:24:47,773 --> 01:24:49,126
They say this army is illegal.

854
01:24:49,893 --> 01:24:51,531
-And they say--
-Drop dead!

855
01:24:51,773 --> 01:24:53,729
And go to hell!

856
01:24:55,933 --> 01:24:57,161
That's what they say.

857
01:24:57,413 --> 01:24:59,324
What are you doing?!
Open the gates.

858
01:25:03,733 --> 01:25:04,768
ldiots!

859
01:25:08,253 --> 01:25:09,402
What're you thinking?!

860
01:25:11,493 --> 01:25:12,369
The Romans. . .

861
01:25:12,973 --> 01:25:14,201
. . .had an expression. . .

862
01:25:14,453 --> 01:25:17,126
. . .they used to scare their children.

863
01:25:18,533 --> 01:25:19,807
"Hannibal...

864
01:25:20,493 --> 01:25:22,449
...ad portas!"

865
01:25:23,773 --> 01:25:25,092
Hannibal. . .

866
01:25:25,933 --> 01:25:27,844
. . .is at the gates.

867
01:25:34,733 --> 01:25:36,485
Do you know who Hannibal was?

868
01:25:38,413 --> 01:25:39,528
Of course not.

869
01:25:39,773 --> 01:25:42,571
A pretty girl like you
wouldn't understand something like that.

870
01:25:47,773 --> 01:25:49,286
-Let's fight them!
-With what?

871
01:25:49,533 --> 01:25:52,605
We've got 5 guns,
maybe 20 rounds of ammo.

872
01:25:52,853 --> 01:25:54,525
How we going to fight with that?

873
01:25:54,773 --> 01:25:55,842
You don't.

874
01:25:59,253 --> 01:26:01,005
Negotiate a settlement.

875
01:26:01,653 --> 01:26:02,881
Give them extra supplies.

876
01:26:08,853 --> 01:26:10,844
You're the government rep.
Tell them.

877
01:26:25,213 --> 01:26:26,282
Right here.

878
01:26:36,573 --> 01:26:39,246
Make it quick.
l've got an attack to coordinate.

879
01:26:40,373 --> 01:26:42,568
They've asked me
to negotiate a peace treaty.

880
01:26:46,373 --> 01:26:47,123
Do l know you?

881
01:26:48,613 --> 01:26:50,092
l don't think so, sir.

882
01:26:50,813 --> 01:26:52,405
You're the postman.

883
01:26:52,853 --> 01:26:53,683
Aren't you?

884
01:26:57,133 --> 01:26:58,168
lnside!

885
01:27:02,493 --> 01:27:04,085
"U.S. Mail. "

886
01:27:05,173 --> 01:27:07,926
"The Restored United States of America. "

887
01:27:08,613 --> 01:27:11,411
Do these people
really believe that shit?!

888
01:27:12,733 --> 01:27:14,689
Who are you, really?

889
01:27:15,293 --> 01:27:17,329
l'm a United States postman. . .

890
01:27:17,653 --> 01:27:21,043
. . .authorized by Order 41 7
of the Restored Congress.

891
01:27:21,293 --> 01:27:25,172
l was at the Battle of Georgetown.
l watched the White House burn down.

892
01:27:25,413 --> 01:27:27,369
Do not try to sell me. . .

893
01:27:27,613 --> 01:27:29,843
. . .on any Restored United States!

894
01:27:32,533 --> 01:27:35,127
The new capital is based
in Minneapolis. . .

895
01:27:35,493 --> 01:27:37,882
. . .inside the Hubert Humphrey Metrodome.

896
01:27:38,453 --> 01:27:40,887
You know where the Vikings
used to play?

897
01:27:42,973 --> 01:27:44,326
You're funny.

898
01:27:49,653 --> 01:27:51,325
What are the terms?

899
01:27:52,333 --> 01:27:54,927
They'll open the gates,
give double the usual. . .

900
01:27:55,453 --> 01:27:56,249
. . .just. . .

901
01:27:56,493 --> 01:27:57,687
. . .don't hurt anybody.

902
01:27:57,973 --> 01:27:59,565
This was all a misunderstanding.

903
01:28:07,093 --> 01:28:09,129
l appreciate your offer, Mr. Oostman.

904
01:28:09,373 --> 01:28:12,843
But the fact is that you're
in no position to negotiate.

905
01:28:13,333 --> 01:28:16,689
These people made it through the bugs
and the riots. . .

906
01:28:17,413 --> 01:28:20,564
. . .and the 3-year winters,
but they're not going to survive you.

907
01:28:21,933 --> 01:28:22,809
Fire at will!

908
01:28:32,933 --> 01:28:34,252
Law Six:

909
01:28:34,453 --> 01:28:36,364
Justice can be. . .

910
01:28:36,613 --> 01:28:37,762
. . .dictated!

911
01:28:40,973 --> 01:28:44,488
Kill him, and kill
the Restored United States with him.

912
01:29:06,413 --> 01:29:07,528
ln accordance with Law 8. . .

913
01:29:07,773 --> 01:29:10,241
. . .and by the authority
of Emergency Order 46. . .

914
01:29:10,493 --> 01:29:11,846
. . .you are hereby--

915
01:29:18,933 --> 01:29:19,809
Get her!

916
01:30:11,853 --> 01:30:13,491
Go on, get him!

917
01:30:33,813 --> 01:30:35,769
We can't stop now.

918
01:30:38,293 --> 01:30:39,408
What are you. . .?

919
01:30:42,333 --> 01:30:43,561
Oh, God!

920
01:31:07,834 --> 01:31:09,062
Come on down.

921
01:31:26,634 --> 01:31:27,828
Don't move.

922
01:31:34,714 --> 01:31:36,432
lf you had a bullet,
you'd use it.

923
01:32:49,034 --> 01:32:50,149
Come on.

924
01:33:40,074 --> 01:33:43,146
l don't think
l ever had water soup before.

925
01:33:43,954 --> 01:33:47,185
Maybe next time
we could try it with a little sand.

926
01:33:48,674 --> 01:33:49,868
Dirt.

927
01:33:51,914 --> 01:33:53,188
Maybe a twig garnish.

928
01:33:58,994 --> 01:34:00,905
You used to think l was funny.

929
01:34:04,754 --> 01:34:06,392
They killed Michael.

930
01:34:15,514 --> 01:34:16,424
l'm sorry.

931
01:34:20,554 --> 01:34:21,703
How sorry are you?

932
01:34:23,154 --> 01:34:24,109
What?

933
01:34:28,994 --> 01:34:30,985
What's that supposed to mean?

934
01:34:33,874 --> 01:34:34,624
What's with you?

935
01:34:34,874 --> 01:34:36,865
You have the mark of 8 on you.

936
01:34:38,674 --> 01:34:39,584
Mark doesn't mean--

937
01:34:39,834 --> 01:34:41,426
You're a liar.

938
01:34:44,354 --> 01:34:45,423
You were with Bethlehem.

939
01:34:46,394 --> 01:34:48,430
Does that make you one of them?

940
01:34:59,834 --> 01:35:01,870
Don't make me use this.

941
01:35:16,314 --> 01:35:17,793
Wind's come up.

942
01:35:18,114 --> 01:35:19,342
lt's getting colder too.

943
01:35:20,194 --> 01:35:22,549
Must be another storm.

944
01:35:26,034 --> 01:35:27,467
Anything else?

945
01:35:29,074 --> 01:35:30,905
l didn't mean for you to. . . .

946
01:35:31,154 --> 01:35:34,624
Your legs are going to rot off
if you don't try to walk.

947
01:35:34,954 --> 01:35:36,592
-l'm hurt.
-You're lazy!

948
01:35:36,834 --> 01:35:37,903
Lazy?

949
01:35:38,194 --> 01:35:40,310
l got a hole in my stomach. . .

950
01:35:40,554 --> 01:35:41,953
. . .and l'm weak.

951
01:35:42,194 --> 01:35:45,630
The 2 big meals around here
are snow and grass. . .

952
01:35:45,874 --> 01:35:47,785
. . .and we're running out of grass.

953
01:35:57,434 --> 01:35:58,662
What're you doing?

954
01:36:24,834 --> 01:36:25,983
Give me a break!

955
01:36:28,474 --> 01:36:29,668
l'm going to check the pass.

956
01:36:31,514 --> 01:36:33,027
Why are you in such a hurry?

957
01:36:33,274 --> 01:36:35,504
l could think of worse places.

958
01:36:36,434 --> 01:36:38,550
Or l could think of worse company.

959
01:36:45,594 --> 01:36:46,868
Oerfect!

960
01:37:42,674 --> 01:37:43,663
Help!

961
01:37:51,034 --> 01:37:51,830
Help!

962
01:37:55,434 --> 01:37:56,423
Olease!

963
01:37:57,794 --> 01:37:58,749
Quick!

964
01:38:09,434 --> 01:38:10,947
God, help me!

965
01:38:29,994 --> 01:38:31,905
l told you that's all there was.

966
01:38:33,114 --> 01:38:35,105
That's why you should have it.

967
01:38:40,314 --> 01:38:42,032
l knew you could walk.

968
01:38:44,394 --> 01:38:45,588
You're weird.

969
01:38:46,474 --> 01:38:47,350
Know that?

970
01:39:09,994 --> 01:39:12,303
We walked on the moon once, Abby.

971
01:39:13,074 --> 01:39:14,473
So?

972
01:39:15,034 --> 01:39:16,911
What good is that now?

973
01:39:20,154 --> 01:39:21,951
Obviously you've forgotten. . .

974
01:39:22,194 --> 01:39:23,468
. . .Tang and. . .

975
01:39:24,154 --> 01:39:25,712
. . .microwave ovens and. . . .

976
01:39:31,914 --> 01:39:33,427
Your face looks pretty.

977
01:39:38,114 --> 01:39:39,388
l mean. . .

978
01:39:39,914 --> 01:39:41,870
. . .not so bruised.

979
01:39:48,754 --> 01:39:49,903
Look. . .

980
01:39:50,474 --> 01:39:51,987
. . .there's something
you'd better know.

981
01:39:53,714 --> 01:39:55,784
You're going to find out soon enough.

982
01:39:56,714 --> 01:39:57,942
l'm pregnant.

983
01:40:00,634 --> 01:40:02,545
lt's Michael's baby.

984
01:40:03,834 --> 01:40:05,904
You're just the body father.

985
01:40:11,154 --> 01:40:12,906
How do you know it's mine. . .

986
01:40:14,994 --> 01:40:16,313
. . .not Bethlehem's?

987
01:40:20,714 --> 01:40:23,308
He tried with me almost every night.

988
01:40:26,794 --> 01:40:28,432
He couldn't do it. . .

989
01:40:32,114 --> 01:40:33,706
. . .so he beat me.

990
01:40:37,634 --> 01:40:39,625
Said it was my fault.

991
01:40:45,714 --> 01:40:46,624
l'm sorry, Abby.

992
01:41:24,754 --> 01:41:26,028
What is it?

993
01:41:27,034 --> 01:41:28,513
What's wrong?

994
01:41:31,314 --> 01:41:32,303
ls it the baby?

995
01:41:33,434 --> 01:41:34,947
The pass is clear.

996
01:41:56,314 --> 01:41:57,713
What happened?

997
01:41:59,994 --> 01:42:01,905
Good, you got our stuff out.

998
01:42:02,154 --> 01:42:03,382
Of course.

999
01:42:04,314 --> 01:42:05,349
What?

1000
01:42:07,154 --> 01:42:08,587
l don't understand.

1001
01:42:09,674 --> 01:42:11,505
l set the fire.

1002
01:42:14,554 --> 01:42:16,590
Did you think we'd stay here forever?

1003
01:42:17,074 --> 01:42:18,189
No.

1004
01:42:21,154 --> 01:42:24,783
l'd appreciate it if you'd walk with me
to find someplace safe for the baby. . .

1005
01:42:25,034 --> 01:42:26,672
. . .then we can split up.

1006
01:42:26,914 --> 01:42:27,744
You shaved.

1007
01:42:29,794 --> 01:42:30,704
Looks nice.

1008
01:42:37,674 --> 01:42:39,187
You're really weird!

1009
01:42:39,434 --> 01:42:40,662
You know that?

1010
01:42:47,674 --> 01:42:49,710
You ever heard of St. Rose, Abby?

1011
01:42:50,314 --> 01:42:51,906
l've heard people talk.

1012
01:42:52,154 --> 01:42:54,190
l've heard lots of names. . .

1013
01:42:54,794 --> 01:42:57,433
. . .Bliss, Hesperia, and New Eden.

1014
01:42:57,754 --> 01:43:00,188
Sheriff Briscoe says it's a fantasy.

1015
01:43:00,434 --> 01:43:01,662
He's wrong.

1016
01:43:01,994 --> 01:43:03,791
St. Rose is out there. . .

1017
01:43:04,314 --> 01:43:05,429
. . .and l'm going to find it.

1018
01:43:05,674 --> 01:43:07,107
But you're The Oostman.

1019
01:43:07,354 --> 01:43:08,912
l'm nobody, Abby.

1020
01:43:23,354 --> 01:43:24,833
This is what l hate.

1021
01:43:25,074 --> 01:43:26,348
Strangers.

1022
01:43:26,594 --> 01:43:28,949
Do you say hi,
or do you blow their heads off?

1023
01:43:29,194 --> 01:43:31,754
Do they want to share what they got
or take what you have?

1024
01:43:33,114 --> 01:43:36,629
lf they want to take, how far
are you willing to go to stop them?

1025
01:43:37,714 --> 01:43:39,466
All right, that's far enough.

1026
01:43:40,594 --> 01:43:42,186
We don't want any trouble.

1027
01:43:45,074 --> 01:43:46,393
Me neither, mister.

1028
01:43:48,514 --> 01:43:49,310
What are you?

1029
01:43:49,554 --> 01:43:50,987
Carrier 1 8. . .

1030
01:43:51,514 --> 01:43:53,232
. . .U.S. Oostal Service.

1031
01:43:54,274 --> 01:43:55,070
Got any mail?

1032
01:43:55,474 --> 01:43:56,987
That's impossible.

1033
01:43:59,514 --> 01:44:01,106
Ain't you heard of The Oostman?

1034
01:44:02,714 --> 01:44:03,749
No.

1035
01:44:04,394 --> 01:44:05,668
Tell us.

1036
01:44:06,514 --> 01:44:08,982
He's only the greatest man
who ever lived.

1037
01:44:09,594 --> 01:44:11,346
He crossed the wasteland. . .

1038
01:44:11,594 --> 01:44:13,505
. . .shook his fist at the enemy. . .

1039
01:44:13,754 --> 01:44:17,110
. . .and spit in the eye
of General Bethlehem himself.

1040
01:44:17,834 --> 01:44:20,587
He's back east
with Oresident Starkey right now.

1041
01:44:21,474 --> 01:44:23,066
Who told you all this?

1042
01:44:23,634 --> 01:44:25,909
Oostmaster Ford Lincoln Mercury.

1043
01:44:26,194 --> 01:44:28,549
He's in direct contact
with the restored Congress.

1044
01:44:28,794 --> 01:44:30,466
Direct contact?!

1045
01:44:30,714 --> 01:44:31,863
l don't believe this!

1046
01:44:32,114 --> 01:44:33,433
Carrier camp!

1047
01:44:33,674 --> 01:44:34,993
Carrier camp!

1048
01:44:35,234 --> 01:44:36,633
Gather around, everybody!

1049
01:44:36,874 --> 01:44:39,388
Come on, gather around.
Got another letter here.

1050
01:44:40,714 --> 01:44:42,227
lt came in last night.

1051
01:44:45,474 --> 01:44:48,671
-What's all this?
-The Oostman sent Ford another letter.

1052
01:44:48,914 --> 01:44:50,506
He's going to read it.

1053
01:44:52,234 --> 01:44:53,872
"Hello, all postal carriers.

1054
01:44:58,554 --> 01:45:01,352
l'm here in Minneapolis
with Oresident Starkey. . .

1055
01:45:01,594 --> 01:45:03,425
. . .but my thoughts are with you.

1056
01:45:03,794 --> 01:45:04,670
Remember. . .

1057
01:45:04,914 --> 01:45:07,633
. . .nothing worth doing
can be done overnight.

1058
01:45:07,874 --> 01:45:11,503
Keep your chins up
and do your best not to get shot.

1059
01:45:11,754 --> 01:45:12,504
Signed. . .

1060
01:45:13,114 --> 01:45:14,069
. . .The Oostman" !

1061
01:45:17,714 --> 01:45:20,103
His letters are always kind of short.

1062
01:45:21,154 --> 01:45:22,553
Hold on!
There's a O.S.

1063
01:45:23,954 --> 01:45:26,593
Does anybody know
what O.S. stands for?

1064
01:45:42,594 --> 01:45:44,789
-Holy shit!
-That would be H.S., Eddie.

1065
01:45:45,834 --> 01:45:48,746
No, l saw him once
when l lived in Oineview.

1066
01:45:48,994 --> 01:45:50,222
lt's The Oostman.

1067
01:46:21,594 --> 01:46:23,471
Guess you want to talk about this.

1068
01:46:33,994 --> 01:46:35,791
l found him!

1069
01:46:41,634 --> 01:46:43,067
"Minneapolis"?

1070
01:46:43,594 --> 01:46:46,666
"O.S. Ford knows what to do"?

1071
01:46:47,914 --> 01:46:49,108
What is this?

1072
01:46:49,594 --> 01:46:51,585
What is all this?
What the hell--

1073
01:46:51,834 --> 01:46:52,983
l lied!

1074
01:46:53,234 --> 01:46:56,271
l told people you were
in direct contact with me.

1075
01:46:58,474 --> 01:47:01,671
-Why?
-Because l didn't want it to end.

1076
01:47:04,674 --> 01:47:05,709
Look. . .

1077
01:47:06,434 --> 01:47:09,870
. . .l don't know how long l can stay.
l mean. . .

1078
01:47:10,114 --> 01:47:11,593
. . .Oresident Starkey. . .

1079
01:47:11,834 --> 01:47:16,271
. . .he's going to send word for me
one day and then l'll have to move on.

1080
01:47:17,274 --> 01:47:18,832
Do you understand?

1081
01:47:25,674 --> 01:47:28,711
But you'll stay
until he sends word, right?

1082
01:47:39,434 --> 01:47:40,867
Don't do that.
Hands down.

1083
01:47:42,634 --> 01:47:45,353
You're staying till Oresident Starkey
sends word, right?

1084
01:47:45,834 --> 01:47:46,744
Yes!

1085
01:47:46,994 --> 01:47:48,791
Until he sends word. Right.

1086
01:47:49,994 --> 01:47:53,191
Could you say a few words
just so they know it's really you?

1087
01:47:58,714 --> 01:47:59,988
lt's me.

1088
01:48:17,834 --> 01:48:19,187
Coming down.

1089
01:48:22,754 --> 01:48:24,949
We bring all the mail here first.

1090
01:48:25,634 --> 01:48:26,828
We sort it.

1091
01:48:27,074 --> 01:48:29,224
We group it.
Then it goes out.

1092
01:48:29,834 --> 01:48:32,064
So far, we got 30 routes.

1093
01:48:42,434 --> 01:48:44,425
You spelled "tyranny" wrong.

1094
01:48:46,154 --> 01:48:47,382
Boy!

1095
01:48:47,914 --> 01:48:49,472
He's smart.

1096
01:48:50,554 --> 01:48:52,385
From the swift completion. . .

1097
01:48:53,474 --> 01:48:54,953
. . .of their appointed rounds.

1098
01:48:57,434 --> 01:49:00,631
Congratulations.
You are now U.S. postal carriers.

1099
01:49:12,954 --> 01:49:14,182
How old are you?

1100
01:49:14,874 --> 01:49:16,751
l'm 68, sir.

1101
01:49:19,994 --> 01:49:21,666
Can l ask you a question?

1102
01:49:24,634 --> 01:49:25,908
Can you ride?

1103
01:49:26,154 --> 01:49:27,064
No.

1104
01:49:27,314 --> 01:49:29,032
Can't walk too good either.

1105
01:49:29,754 --> 01:49:31,506
So why are you here?

1106
01:49:32,074 --> 01:49:33,587
l know stuff.

1107
01:49:39,194 --> 01:49:40,513
Where did you get that?

1108
01:49:43,834 --> 01:49:45,950
1 970.

1109
01:49:46,914 --> 01:49:49,223
A girl with eyes as big as saucers. . .

1110
01:49:49,474 --> 01:49:51,908
. . .did me in a little town
called Saigon.

1111
01:50:09,994 --> 01:50:12,462
Ford wants me to have his place.

1112
01:50:13,634 --> 01:50:14,749
Said it's the best.

1113
01:50:18,634 --> 01:50:19,783
l'm on the other side.

1114
01:50:23,114 --> 01:50:25,070
l got plenty of room here.

1115
01:50:29,914 --> 01:50:32,508
So much for the uniform theory.

1116
01:50:39,434 --> 01:50:41,425
He was captured on the Oregon border.

1117
01:50:43,674 --> 01:50:45,392
Who the hell are you?

1118
01:50:45,634 --> 01:50:46,464
Carrier 1 2.

1119
01:50:47,874 --> 01:50:49,387
United States Oostal Service.

1120
01:51:04,034 --> 01:51:06,787
l want the camp struck at dawn.

1121
01:51:09,554 --> 01:51:10,907
We'll be moving north!

1122
01:51:16,394 --> 01:51:18,703
You spelled "tyranny" wrong.

1123
01:51:22,034 --> 01:51:23,672
l wish they'd stop saluting.

1124
01:51:32,834 --> 01:51:34,153
Just stay safe.

1125
01:51:35,354 --> 01:51:36,628
Remember. . .

1126
01:51:37,234 --> 01:51:39,145
. . .the mailman's more important
than the mail.

1127
01:51:40,914 --> 01:51:42,552
Boy, he's smart.

1128
01:51:46,634 --> 01:51:49,706
When l was a kid we used to turn
our hat around backwards.

1129
01:51:51,114 --> 01:51:52,911
Thought it was cool.

1130
01:51:59,834 --> 01:52:01,392
Jesus Christ!

1131
01:52:10,874 --> 01:52:11,909
Damn!

1132
01:53:17,594 --> 01:53:18,549
l missed him.

1133
01:55:04,034 --> 01:55:06,025
What's the name of this town?

1134
01:55:08,394 --> 01:55:09,747
We never named it.

1135
01:55:12,114 --> 01:55:13,706
l officially declare. . .

1136
01:55:13,954 --> 01:55:16,024
. . .Oostal Station Number 1 0. . .

1137
01:55:17,074 --> 01:55:18,473
. . .in Elvis, Oregon. . .

1138
01:55:18,714 --> 01:55:20,306
. . .open for business.

1139
01:55:22,994 --> 01:55:26,873
From now on you got to get your mail
down there, okay?

1140
01:55:27,834 --> 01:55:29,426
This one doesn't work.

1141
01:55:40,914 --> 01:55:42,347
Read it again.

1142
01:55:43,114 --> 01:55:44,229
Are you sure?

1143
01:55:44,474 --> 01:55:45,509
Yes.

1144
01:55:47,074 --> 01:55:49,588
"Dearest Mom:
What a miracle to hear from you. "

1145
01:55:55,674 --> 01:55:57,585
Stuff is getting better.

1146
01:55:58,074 --> 01:56:00,463
Stuff is getting better every day.

1147
01:56:04,354 --> 01:56:05,548
l don't know who you are. . .

1148
01:56:08,114 --> 01:56:10,469
. . .but l do know
l was wrong about you.

1149
01:56:15,074 --> 01:56:17,065
Got a letter for you too, Sheriff.

1150
01:56:29,994 --> 01:56:31,712
lt's from my sister.

1151
01:56:33,114 --> 01:56:34,513
Thought she was dead.

1152
01:56:36,314 --> 01:56:37,633
You thought wrong.

1153
01:56:57,874 --> 01:56:59,830
Would you like to dance?

1154
01:57:04,794 --> 01:57:06,910
Well, they say that you can never

1155
01:57:09,234 --> 01:57:10,826
Never go back home

1156
01:57:16,314 --> 01:57:18,384
And if you're bound to Wander

1157
01:57:21,354 --> 01:57:23,185
You're bound to be alone

1158
01:57:27,874 --> 01:57:30,024
You say l got no right

1159
01:57:31,394 --> 01:57:33,464
To feel What l feel

1160
01:57:34,394 --> 01:57:36,385
When l look into your eyes

1161
01:57:37,834 --> 01:57:38,983
Want to dance?

1162
01:57:39,674 --> 01:57:41,869
But that l dream of you

1163
01:57:42,794 --> 01:57:44,432
Most every night

1164
01:57:46,394 --> 01:57:48,305
Comes as no surprise

1165
01:57:51,754 --> 01:57:55,542
Well, l've been
Out on this road for so long

1166
01:57:58,194 --> 01:57:59,388
Far and Wide

1167
01:58:00,554 --> 01:58:01,703
Do l roam

1168
01:58:04,074 --> 01:58:07,828
But something in your smile tells me

1169
01:58:09,074 --> 01:58:11,668
l'm almost home

1170
01:58:29,514 --> 01:58:30,947
l Was lost in the dark

1171
01:58:31,394 --> 01:58:32,463
All alone

1172
01:58:34,154 --> 01:58:35,473
Till the light

1173
01:58:35,714 --> 01:58:38,103
ln your eyes shoWed me

1174
01:58:39,034 --> 01:58:40,387
l Was almost

1175
01:58:41,074 --> 01:58:42,985
Home is Where the heart is

1176
01:58:44,434 --> 01:58:45,389
And my heart goes With you

1177
01:58:46,554 --> 01:58:48,624
l Would travel till the end of time

1178
01:58:49,714 --> 01:58:52,069
lf that's What l have to do

1179
01:58:52,754 --> 01:58:55,427
Just to spend one night

1180
01:58:55,834 --> 01:58:58,189
Till your sWeet love light

1181
01:58:58,434 --> 01:58:59,787
Come doWn

1182
01:59:02,394 --> 01:59:04,669
Shining doWn on me

1183
01:59:18,314 --> 01:59:19,429
Hello.

1184
01:59:22,394 --> 01:59:24,032
Who do you talk to?

1185
01:59:24,314 --> 01:59:27,147
Not a soul in 7 years of trying. . .

1186
01:59:27,434 --> 01:59:28,662
. . .but l will.

1187
01:59:32,554 --> 01:59:33,623
Want some?

1188
01:59:33,874 --> 01:59:35,387
No, thanks.

1189
01:59:35,954 --> 01:59:38,229
Don't let the kids see that.

1190
01:59:38,594 --> 01:59:40,186
You go ahead, take a look.

1191
01:59:40,954 --> 01:59:43,343
l was an aerospace engineer.

1192
01:59:43,714 --> 01:59:46,786
l helped design
the Galileo Space Station.

1193
01:59:47,154 --> 01:59:48,143
No shit?

1194
01:59:48,394 --> 01:59:49,588
No shit.

1195
01:59:50,434 --> 01:59:53,426
l dream it's orbiting
the Earth forever. . .

1196
01:59:54,154 --> 01:59:55,746
. . .with a dozen human skeletons. . .

1197
01:59:56,674 --> 01:59:58,232
. . .all grinning at each other. . .

1198
01:59:58,914 --> 02:00:00,666
. . .laughing at us down here.

1199
02:00:11,914 --> 02:00:13,905
-What is it?
-lt's Tony.

1200
02:00:14,434 --> 02:00:15,787
He's overdue.

1201
02:00:17,834 --> 02:00:19,233
That makes 5.

1202
02:00:20,274 --> 02:00:22,105
All on southern routes.

1203
02:00:28,354 --> 02:00:29,992
Just children.

1204
02:00:30,634 --> 02:00:32,431
You bring me children.

1205
02:00:32,794 --> 02:00:34,466
l want a man.

1206
02:00:38,954 --> 02:00:40,626
We got births and. . .

1207
02:00:40,874 --> 02:00:41,863
. . .deaths.

1208
02:00:42,114 --> 02:00:44,503
Got weather.
Mostly gossip.

1209
02:00:44,794 --> 02:00:46,273
There's nothing here.

1210
02:00:46,714 --> 02:00:47,942
Nothing?

1211
02:00:48,794 --> 02:00:49,988
Everything. . .

1212
02:00:50,234 --> 02:00:51,553
. . .is here.

1213
02:00:52,474 --> 02:00:55,784
Am l the only one who sees that?!

1214
02:00:56,154 --> 02:00:57,143
What?

1215
02:01:06,474 --> 02:01:09,227
A military man,
especially a commander. . .

1216
02:01:09,474 --> 02:01:10,827
. . .should keep a journal.

1217
02:01:11,114 --> 02:01:13,150
After he's gone,
it's the only real defense. . .

1218
02:01:13,394 --> 02:01:16,227
. . .against the slander
that later arises.

1219
02:01:40,354 --> 02:01:42,504
Tell me about the other stuff you know.

1220
02:02:34,754 --> 02:02:35,630
Shit!

1221
02:04:16,554 --> 02:04:17,873
Get rid of the bodies.

1222
02:04:18,874 --> 02:04:21,627
l don't want these people blamed
for what we did.

1223
02:04:23,914 --> 02:04:26,951
Neither snoW, nor rain,
nor gloom of night...

1224
02:04:28,954 --> 02:04:31,548
... through bandit's hell,
through firefight...

1225
02:04:33,274 --> 02:04:35,663
... through flood and plague
We cannot fail...

1226
02:04:37,514 --> 02:04:39,982
...no Holnist trash
Will stop the mail.

1227
02:04:42,594 --> 02:04:44,744
You are now U.S. Oostal Carriers.

1228
02:04:47,394 --> 02:04:48,873
They changed the oath.

1229
02:04:49,554 --> 02:04:50,543
Ford's idea.

1230
02:04:51,434 --> 02:04:52,583
Figures.

1231
02:04:53,554 --> 02:04:55,829
They don't think to ask
who they're replacing. . .

1232
02:04:56,074 --> 02:04:57,189
. . .or why.

1233
02:04:58,074 --> 02:04:59,189
Sir?

1234
02:05:02,354 --> 02:05:04,584
lt'd be an honor
if l could shake your hand.

1235
02:05:06,714 --> 02:05:07,385
Do l know you?

1236
02:05:10,234 --> 02:05:11,633
l don't think so.

1237
02:05:14,394 --> 02:05:15,383
Good luck, then.

1238
02:05:24,794 --> 02:05:26,068
Nice kid.

1239
02:05:26,834 --> 02:05:28,790
He'll probably be dead in a week.

1240
02:05:29,034 --> 02:05:31,025
Now that is not your fault.

1241
02:05:31,434 --> 02:05:34,710
You're exhausted. You need rest.
There's food--

1242
02:05:36,514 --> 02:05:38,345
-Where are you going?
-Route 22.

1243
02:05:38,834 --> 02:05:41,029
You're grounded.
Get off the horse.

1244
02:05:41,954 --> 02:05:42,784
You know the rule.

1245
02:05:43,114 --> 02:05:43,864
What rule?

1246
02:05:45,234 --> 02:05:47,304
22, it's too far south.
Get off the horse.

1247
02:05:47,554 --> 02:05:48,828
But they're waiting on--

1248
02:05:49,074 --> 02:05:50,632
Get off the goddamn horse!

1249
02:05:52,954 --> 02:05:54,751
l'll tie him off to this one.

1250
02:05:55,154 --> 02:05:56,553
You can't keep doing this!

1251
02:05:57,474 --> 02:05:59,066
-Doing what?
-Riding all the routes.

1252
02:05:59,314 --> 02:06:01,066
You're not saving anybody.

1253
02:06:02,954 --> 02:06:05,866
Did l ever tell you
how l got to be a postman?

1254
02:06:07,674 --> 02:06:09,392
l don't know if you'd laugh
or cry.

1255
02:06:14,634 --> 02:06:15,623
What is it?

1256
02:06:17,434 --> 02:06:18,184
Watch out!

1257
02:06:25,714 --> 02:06:27,113
We got fire! Move!

1258
02:07:01,234 --> 02:07:03,794
-"Oostage due. "
-Elvis patrol.

1259
02:07:08,994 --> 02:07:10,632
You want a war?

1260
02:07:12,194 --> 02:07:14,150
You want a war?!

1261
02:07:14,714 --> 02:07:16,306
l'll give you. . .

1262
02:07:16,554 --> 02:07:18,226
. . .a war!

1263
02:07:19,034 --> 02:07:20,387
l was. . .

1264
02:07:20,634 --> 02:07:22,909
. . .born for it!

1265
02:07:23,794 --> 02:07:25,386
You murderers!

1266
02:07:27,874 --> 02:07:29,592
You think you can ride?!

1267
02:07:31,034 --> 02:07:33,309
Then today's your lucky day!

1268
02:07:34,034 --> 02:07:35,547
Bethlehem says...

1269
02:07:36,394 --> 02:07:37,827
...he's headed north.

1270
02:07:39,074 --> 02:07:41,304
He's going to kill 10 people
in every toWn...

1271
02:07:41,554 --> 02:07:43,909
... then burn it to the ground
for What you did.

1272
02:07:45,594 --> 02:07:47,710
He said that PinevieW's on his Way.

1273
02:07:49,234 --> 02:07:51,225
He'd wait there for you,
but not for long.

1274
02:07:53,434 --> 02:07:55,152
l was so scared, sir.

1275
02:07:55,474 --> 02:07:57,749
l thought
they were going to kill me too.

1276
02:08:04,794 --> 02:08:05,624
See?

1277
02:08:05,874 --> 02:08:07,910
We're too late. l told you.

1278
02:08:08,354 --> 02:08:09,548
What're you going to do?

1279
02:08:09,794 --> 02:08:11,273
l'm going to stop this.

1280
02:08:11,994 --> 02:08:12,744
You can't.

1281
02:08:13,034 --> 02:08:14,990
Get out of the way, Ford.
All of you!

1282
02:08:15,234 --> 02:08:16,428
They'll kill you!

1283
02:08:20,194 --> 02:08:21,229
Hold him!

1284
02:08:24,394 --> 02:08:25,190
Stop it!

1285
02:08:26,794 --> 02:08:27,783
-You're hurting him!
-l'm not!

1286
02:08:28,034 --> 02:08:28,910
Yes, you are!

1287
02:08:29,154 --> 02:08:31,429
l'm not!
l'm not hurting him.

1288
02:08:32,354 --> 02:08:36,029
This is all my doing.
l went against your orders.

1289
02:08:36,794 --> 02:08:40,423
You told me to bury the dead Holnists,
but l sent them Bethlehem.

1290
02:08:40,674 --> 02:08:41,584
Why?

1291
02:08:41,914 --> 02:08:43,188
Bethlehem has to know
we won't stop!

1292
02:08:43,594 --> 02:08:45,266
Goddamn it, Ford!

1293
02:08:46,714 --> 02:08:49,023
Those people are dying because of us!

1294
02:08:49,274 --> 02:08:51,469
They're dying because of what we did.

1295
02:08:51,714 --> 02:08:54,023
They're not!
They're dying because of Bethlehem. . .

1296
02:08:54,274 --> 02:08:57,232
. . .because this is a shitty world!
lf we're going to change it. . .

1297
02:08:57,474 --> 02:08:58,987
. . .then someone might have to die.

1298
02:08:59,234 --> 02:09:01,907
lf l could make it be me down there,
l would, but l can't!

1299
02:09:05,154 --> 02:09:06,473
No! Olease!

1300
02:09:08,794 --> 02:09:10,193
-You, out here!
-Hold her!

1301
02:09:10,434 --> 02:09:11,662
Olease!

1302
02:09:28,074 --> 02:09:29,951
He's out there somewhere.

1303
02:09:31,674 --> 02:09:32,823
Watching.

1304
02:09:35,194 --> 02:09:36,912
l can feel it.

1305
02:09:40,154 --> 02:09:41,906
You feel it too, don't you?

1306
02:09:43,474 --> 02:09:45,669
lt didn't have to end
like this, Sheriff!

1307
02:09:46,154 --> 02:09:49,783
He knew where l'd be
if he wanted to face me like a man!

1308
02:09:50,594 --> 02:09:52,027
lnstead he's hiding. . .

1309
02:09:52,274 --> 02:09:53,627
. . .like a rabbit!

1310
02:09:54,034 --> 02:09:55,945
So much for your Oostman!

1311
02:09:56,714 --> 02:09:57,908
Lieutenant!

1312
02:09:58,834 --> 02:09:59,664
Ready!

1313
02:10:01,074 --> 02:10:02,587
We don't even know their names.

1314
02:10:03,714 --> 02:10:05,352
We know their names.

1315
02:10:10,354 --> 02:10:11,264
l think that's my dad.

1316
02:10:20,154 --> 02:10:21,269
Aim!

1317
02:10:22,074 --> 02:10:23,348
Ride, Oostman!

1318
02:10:23,914 --> 02:10:25,108
Ride!

1319
02:10:25,554 --> 02:10:26,623
You hear me?!

1320
02:10:26,874 --> 02:10:28,626
l said, "Ride! "

1321
02:10:30,074 --> 02:10:30,904
Fire!

1322
02:10:53,634 --> 02:10:55,704
My God, what have l done?

1323
02:10:58,554 --> 02:11:00,146
What Ford did was wrong!

1324
02:11:03,874 --> 02:11:05,865
But it doesn't change anything. . .

1325
02:11:06,114 --> 02:11:09,186
. . .for any of us, does it?

1326
02:11:31,074 --> 02:11:32,268
ls this everybody?

1327
02:11:33,354 --> 02:11:34,753
The rest are on the overdue list.

1328
02:11:36,154 --> 02:11:37,633
Then this is everybody.

1329
02:11:38,794 --> 02:11:40,830
Got a letter from the Oresident.

1330
02:11:43,194 --> 02:11:44,707
"Greetings, all carriers. "

1331
02:11:44,954 --> 02:11:46,546
Greetings, Oresident Starkey!

1332
02:11:50,674 --> 02:11:52,983
"l've been in contact with The Oostman.

1333
02:11:53,234 --> 02:11:54,952
And l've received all the reports.

1334
02:11:55,514 --> 02:11:57,106
l'm proud of you all.

1335
02:11:58,034 --> 02:11:59,945
ln dark days,
in a weary world. . .

1336
02:12:00,194 --> 02:12:02,549
. . .you gave everything
and asked for nothing.

1337
02:12:03,554 --> 02:12:05,943
You beat back despair
and replaced it with hope.

1338
02:12:06,714 --> 02:12:08,944
For that, your country
can never repay you.

1339
02:12:09,834 --> 02:12:11,347
But the price is too high. . .

1340
02:12:12,954 --> 02:12:15,991
. . .and l won't see any more
of my bravest die.

1341
02:12:17,554 --> 02:12:19,909
lt is my duty to hereby disband. . .

1342
02:12:20,154 --> 02:12:23,510
. . .the Oostal Service
of the Restored United States.

1343
02:12:24,314 --> 02:12:26,305
You are to burn your uniforms. . .

1344
02:12:26,554 --> 02:12:29,864
. . .and The Oostman
is to return to Minneapolis at once.

1345
02:12:30,634 --> 02:12:31,953
Thank you.

1346
02:12:32,594 --> 02:12:34,152
And God bless you all.

1347
02:12:35,034 --> 02:12:36,183
The Oresident. "

1348
02:12:53,194 --> 02:12:55,344
The Oresident never wrote that letter.

1349
02:12:55,834 --> 02:12:58,029
lf he could've,
that's what he would have said.

1350
02:12:58,354 --> 02:12:59,946
Who's the other letter to?

1351
02:13:00,194 --> 02:13:01,388
Bethlehem.

1352
02:13:01,874 --> 02:13:04,149
-l'm taking it to him in the morning.
-What's it say?

1353
02:13:04,714 --> 02:13:07,547
-Mail's private, you know that.
-What does it say?

1354
02:13:08,914 --> 02:13:10,632
lt says it's over.

1355
02:13:10,954 --> 02:13:12,626
lt says we quit.

1356
02:13:13,714 --> 02:13:15,545
lt says you quit!

1357
02:13:16,154 --> 02:13:17,189
What about the oath?

1358
02:13:17,434 --> 02:13:19,072
Tell me something, Ford.

1359
02:13:19,314 --> 02:13:22,147
How much mail
can a dead postman deliver?

1360
02:13:23,354 --> 02:13:24,582
lt's over.

1361
02:13:29,394 --> 02:13:30,588
Then l'll take it.

1362
02:13:31,114 --> 02:13:32,467
l can't trust you.

1363
02:13:40,234 --> 02:13:41,872
lf this is the end. . .

1364
02:13:43,554 --> 02:13:46,546
. . .if this is the last piece of mail
that ever gets delivered. . .

1365
02:13:48,994 --> 02:13:50,427
. . .l'll take it.

1366
02:13:52,314 --> 02:13:55,465
Whoever delivers this letter, Ford,
probably dies for it.

1367
02:13:55,834 --> 02:13:57,870
l'm still a postman!

1368
02:14:01,114 --> 02:14:02,069
You owe it to me.

1369
02:14:03,954 --> 02:14:04,909
l owe it to me.

1370
02:14:19,994 --> 02:14:21,666
lt's not Ford's fault.

1371
02:14:22,194 --> 02:14:25,823
He's not like you. He doesn 't have
your memories. None of them do.

1372
02:14:26,954 --> 02:14:28,512
This is all they have.

1373
02:14:29,394 --> 02:14:31,624
-lt's the only decent thing they know.
-What?

1374
02:14:31,874 --> 02:14:33,227
Being a postman?

1375
02:14:34,754 --> 02:14:36,426
lt's all bullshit, Abby.

1376
02:14:36,674 --> 02:14:37,743
All of it.

1377
02:14:38,594 --> 02:14:41,427
l took the uniform off a skeleton
to stay warm.

1378
02:14:41,794 --> 02:14:44,467
l made up the rest to stay fed.

1379
02:14:45,034 --> 02:14:46,149
There is no. . .

1380
02:14:46,394 --> 02:14:48,862
. . .Restored United States.

1381
02:14:49,754 --> 02:14:51,392
l figured it was something like that.

1382
02:14:51,634 --> 02:14:53,431
l'm going to St. Rose.

1383
02:14:53,674 --> 02:14:55,471
l'm taking you with me.

1384
02:14:56,234 --> 02:14:58,031
l've already packed your horse.

1385
02:14:58,834 --> 02:15:00,904
l know you don't want to hear it. . .

1386
02:15:01,634 --> 02:15:03,829
. . .but that's my child inside you.

1387
02:15:04,714 --> 02:15:06,670
l want to see it born somewhere safe.

1388
02:15:29,314 --> 02:15:31,066
l thought l recognized you.

1389
02:15:31,914 --> 02:15:34,906
General Bethlehem said you should be
on your knees when l do this.

1390
02:15:35,354 --> 02:15:37,106
l don't give a damn
what that asshole said.

1391
02:15:38,234 --> 02:15:39,826
The general is a great man!

1392
02:15:44,194 --> 02:15:46,389
The general is a fucking lunatic.

1393
02:15:51,514 --> 02:15:52,993
You want to see a man?

1394
02:15:53,994 --> 02:15:55,347
That's a man.

1395
02:15:59,354 --> 02:16:00,423
You ready?

1396
02:16:04,554 --> 02:16:05,669
Yes.

1397
02:16:09,114 --> 02:16:11,344
You're a better man than Bethlehem.

1398
02:16:12,394 --> 02:16:13,588
l've seen it.

1399
02:16:18,434 --> 02:16:19,503
"To Bethlehem.

1400
02:16:20,434 --> 02:16:22,345
This letter is my testimony...

1401
02:16:22,914 --> 02:16:25,189
... to the fact that there is no...

1402
02:16:25,434 --> 02:16:27,470
...Restored United States...

1403
02:16:27,794 --> 02:16:29,864
. . .and there is no postal service. "

1404
02:16:31,514 --> 02:16:32,867
He expects me to believe this?

1405
02:16:33,194 --> 02:16:33,944
lt's true.

1406
02:16:38,314 --> 02:16:40,430
l was there.
He disbanded the carriers. . .

1407
02:16:41,634 --> 02:16:42,987
. . .and rode west.

1408
02:16:43,314 --> 02:16:44,110
Traitor!

1409
02:16:46,954 --> 02:16:47,909
Then l've won.

1410
02:16:54,594 --> 02:16:56,869
Bring the one we found yesterday.
They can die together.

1411
02:16:58,074 --> 02:16:59,393
You traitor!
You're a traitor!

1412
02:17:06,234 --> 02:17:08,190
That one's the second-in-command.

1413
02:17:08,434 --> 02:17:10,550
Why doesn't that surprise me?

1414
02:17:13,874 --> 02:17:15,353
l was thinking, sir. . .

1415
02:17:16,834 --> 02:17:19,746
. . .he might be more valuable to us
as a prisoner.

1416
02:17:20,914 --> 02:17:22,825
You were supposed to kill him. . .

1417
02:17:23,074 --> 02:17:24,143
. . .weren't you?

1418
02:17:25,554 --> 02:17:27,306
l couldn't get close enough.

1419
02:17:47,594 --> 02:17:48,663
Who are you?

1420
02:17:49,634 --> 02:17:51,192
My name's Clark.

1421
02:17:51,434 --> 02:17:54,107
Oostal Carrier
for the Restored Republic of California.

1422
02:17:54,674 --> 02:17:55,709
Who are you?

1423
02:18:01,674 --> 02:18:04,108
Oostmaster Ford Lincoln Mercury.

1424
02:18:12,394 --> 02:18:13,622
lt's an honor.

1425
02:18:17,034 --> 02:18:17,864
Wait!

1426
02:18:19,954 --> 02:18:22,024
Wait a minute.
Hold your fire.

1427
02:18:26,914 --> 02:18:28,393
You two don't know each other?

1428
02:18:36,434 --> 02:18:38,550
This'll never be over.

1429
02:18:39,074 --> 02:18:40,507
lt'll go on.

1430
02:18:42,034 --> 02:18:44,423
Except l'll be fighting
a goddamn ghost.

1431
02:18:45,434 --> 02:18:47,823
-Should we fire, sir?
-No, goddamn it!

1432
02:18:49,234 --> 02:18:50,906
l won't fight a ghost.

1433
02:18:53,354 --> 02:18:54,628
Tabula...

1434
02:18:55,314 --> 02:18:56,463
...rasa...

1435
02:18:56,714 --> 02:18:57,908
. . .gentlemen.

1436
02:18:58,834 --> 02:19:00,665
A clean slate.

1437
02:19:01,594 --> 02:19:04,472
l want all mail carriers hunted down.

1438
02:19:05,234 --> 02:19:07,543
l want The Oostman found.

1439
02:19:07,794 --> 02:19:09,625
l want him dealt with.

1440
02:19:10,554 --> 02:19:12,112
Colonel, organize the scouts.

1441
02:19:13,874 --> 02:19:14,989
You said he rode west?

1442
02:19:20,314 --> 02:19:22,032
And this is his second-in-command?

1443
02:19:25,954 --> 02:19:27,069
Yes, sir!

1444
02:19:39,794 --> 02:19:42,945
l'll keep you to bargain with.
The Oostman is weak that way.

1445
02:20:31,514 --> 02:20:33,345
Set your rifle on the ground!

1446
02:20:34,034 --> 02:20:35,865
Set it on the ground.

1447
02:20:37,434 --> 02:20:39,504
What? This old thing?

1448
02:20:41,034 --> 02:20:42,103
lt isn't even loaded.

1449
02:20:43,394 --> 02:20:44,827
Where are we?

1450
02:20:45,874 --> 02:20:47,785
You're in Bridge City. . .

1451
02:20:49,634 --> 02:20:51,590
. . .where we don't allow guns.

1452
02:21:01,674 --> 02:21:03,346
The sentry said you were coming.

1453
02:21:11,034 --> 02:21:12,911
l know you. You're. . .

1454
02:21:13,474 --> 02:21:14,190
. . .famous.

1455
02:21:15,914 --> 02:21:17,267
l was once. . .

1456
02:21:17,514 --> 02:21:18,629
. . .sort of. . .

1457
02:21:18,874 --> 02:21:20,102
. . .kind of.

1458
02:21:20,434 --> 02:21:21,753
Not anymore.

1459
02:21:22,634 --> 02:21:23,430
Looking to cross?

1460
02:21:24,314 --> 02:21:25,463
We will be.

1461
02:21:26,394 --> 02:21:29,147
Right now we'd appreciate some food.

1462
02:21:30,834 --> 02:21:32,108
Okay.

1463
02:21:32,994 --> 02:21:34,393
There are some kids behind us.

1464
02:21:34,634 --> 02:21:35,510
How many?

1465
02:21:35,754 --> 02:21:36,504
3.

1466
02:21:37,434 --> 02:21:39,152
3. Okay.

1467
02:21:42,034 --> 02:21:43,626
Come on in, guys!

1468
02:21:45,914 --> 02:21:47,905
l know you're out there.

1469
02:22:56,834 --> 02:22:58,984
-Wait. Just wait.
-What did he want?

1470
02:23:00,674 --> 02:23:02,392
Hold on. He says. . .

1471
02:23:02,634 --> 02:23:04,750
. . .he's looking for The Oostman.

1472
02:23:05,234 --> 02:23:07,190
There's no such thing anymore.

1473
02:23:10,714 --> 02:23:13,467
The man on the horse says there is.

1474
02:23:13,954 --> 02:23:15,751
He thinks he's here.

1475
02:23:16,154 --> 02:23:18,190
And he's coming back with friends.

1476
02:23:23,394 --> 02:23:25,225
What's a postman?

1477
02:23:42,354 --> 02:23:43,673
You never heard of a postman?

1478
02:24:19,754 --> 02:24:20,823
Are you The Oostman?

1479
02:24:26,394 --> 02:24:27,383
Yeah.

1480
02:24:28,754 --> 02:24:30,472
l heard of you, man.

1481
02:24:31,354 --> 02:24:32,673
You're famous.

1482
02:24:34,554 --> 02:24:36,226
Yeah, l guess l am.

1483
02:24:37,874 --> 02:24:39,546
And all of a sudden,
l'm not. . .

1484
02:24:39,994 --> 02:24:41,871
. . .wearing the right clothes.

1485
02:24:55,834 --> 02:24:58,029
Man, you're going to love this!

1486
02:24:58,434 --> 02:25:00,994
Open that second chute, bro!

1487
02:25:16,954 --> 02:25:19,104
You have a gift, Oostman.

1488
02:25:20,634 --> 02:25:22,943
l saw it back in Oineview.

1489
02:25:25,354 --> 02:25:28,073
You've given us all back
what we'd forgotten.

1490
02:25:29,914 --> 02:25:32,792
You made Mrs. March feel like
she could see again.

1491
02:25:34,514 --> 02:25:37,904
You made Ford feel like
he was part of the world.

1492
02:25:40,754 --> 02:25:43,029
You give out hope like it was. . .

1493
02:25:43,274 --> 02:25:45,151
. . .candy in your pocket.

1494
02:26:00,674 --> 02:26:01,902
Remember this?

1495
02:26:03,594 --> 02:26:04,947
l remember.

1496
02:26:06,514 --> 02:26:09,233
l always like to think
that you left it on purpose.

1497
02:26:14,714 --> 02:26:16,670
This is hard for me.

1498
02:26:20,874 --> 02:26:23,866
Michael was the best man l ever knew.

1499
02:26:26,474 --> 02:26:29,910
l never thought there'd be another man
l could love the way l loved him.

1500
02:26:33,594 --> 02:26:36,154
l couldn't see it for so long.

1501
02:26:38,714 --> 02:26:40,511
And now you're leaving.

1502
02:26:44,794 --> 02:26:45,863
And l'm afraid.

1503
02:26:49,274 --> 02:26:51,742
l'm afraid you'll never
find your St. Rose.

1504
02:26:52,514 --> 02:26:53,310
lt's not important.

1505
02:26:53,554 --> 02:26:56,148
l'm afraid you'll never
see your baby.

1506
02:27:23,194 --> 02:27:26,869
l need full power, man!
This dude's got a long way to go!

1507
02:27:31,594 --> 02:27:33,585
This thing's working perfect, man!

1508
02:27:44,994 --> 02:27:46,950
A lot higher than it looks, huh?

1509
02:27:56,634 --> 02:27:57,953
You nearly went.

1510
02:28:00,674 --> 02:28:01,345
Get in.

1511
02:28:02,914 --> 02:28:05,428
There's 3 good-sized towns up ahead. . .

1512
02:28:05,674 --> 02:28:09,064
. . .with enough people to help you
if you can convince them to come.

1513
02:28:12,514 --> 02:28:14,152
Don't tell anybody. . .

1514
02:28:14,394 --> 02:28:17,511
. . .l like to ride this damn thing
just for the hell of it.

1515
02:28:17,754 --> 02:28:20,826
Being a city official
has its perks, you know?

1516
02:28:28,554 --> 02:28:32,103
Trust me, man.
This'll get you there a lot faster.

1517
02:28:37,514 --> 02:28:38,663
How do l stop?

1518
02:28:39,114 --> 02:28:41,264
Quit worrying about the little things.

1519
02:28:41,514 --> 02:28:43,391
Good luck, and Godspeed.

1520
02:28:58,914 --> 02:29:00,870
Reporting for duty, sir!

1521
02:29:01,114 --> 02:29:02,672
-KnoW What to do?
-Talk to the people.

1522
02:29:03,154 --> 02:29:04,473
Tell them
it's important.

1523
02:29:04,714 --> 02:29:05,942
Tell them
We can make a difference.

1524
02:29:06,994 --> 02:29:10,350
"Once more unto the breach,
dear friends, once more...

1525
02:29:10,594 --> 02:29:12,789
...or close the Wall With our dead!

1526
02:29:13,114 --> 02:29:16,948
ln peace, nothing so becomes a man
as modesty and humility.

1527
02:29:17,194 --> 02:29:19,833
But When the blast of War
bloWs in our ears...

1528
02:29:20,074 --> 02:29:22,110
... then imitate
the action of the tiger.

1529
02:29:22,354 --> 02:29:26,427
Summon up the blood.
Disguise fair nature With rage...

1530
02:29:26,674 --> 02:29:29,666
...and lend the eye
a terrible aspect. "

1531
02:30:11,394 --> 02:30:12,747
-Who are they?
-l don't know.

1532
02:30:12,994 --> 02:30:15,952
Looks like mostly women
and young people to me.

1533
02:30:16,194 --> 02:30:17,309
How many?

1534
02:30:17,714 --> 02:30:18,908
lt's an army.

1535
02:30:29,314 --> 02:30:30,747
At last. . .

1536
02:30:30,994 --> 02:30:34,464
. . .someone with courage enough
to bring the fight to me.

1537
02:30:38,754 --> 02:30:40,187
Reckoning, gentlemen!

1538
02:31:31,714 --> 02:31:33,830
They're an eager-looking bunch!

1539
02:32:00,594 --> 02:32:03,233
Morale is a dangerous thing.

1540
02:32:05,114 --> 02:32:06,911
Bring up the prisoner!

1541
02:32:07,514 --> 02:32:09,345
We'll show them
how this game is played.

1542
02:32:50,034 --> 02:32:51,353
Stay here.

1543
02:33:05,314 --> 02:33:06,303
ls he surrendering?

1544
02:33:06,714 --> 02:33:08,386
God, l hope not.

1545
02:33:29,434 --> 02:33:30,947
My little shipping clerk.

1546
02:33:31,514 --> 02:33:33,311
Mr. copy-machine salesman.

1547
02:33:34,554 --> 02:33:36,306
We're both a couple of frauds.

1548
02:33:38,474 --> 02:33:39,702
So be it.

1549
02:33:40,994 --> 02:33:44,464
But great men are made
by other great men.

1550
02:33:44,994 --> 02:33:46,188
Oatton had Rommel.

1551
02:33:46,794 --> 02:33:48,750
Grant had Lee.

1552
02:33:49,434 --> 02:33:50,389
But l get you.

1553
02:33:51,074 --> 02:33:52,473
You're no general.

1554
02:33:53,554 --> 02:33:54,828
You're not even a good painter.

1555
02:33:57,234 --> 02:33:58,747
Trying to goad me
into a fight?

1556
02:33:58,994 --> 02:34:02,543
lt'd be great if wars were fought
just by the assholes who started them.

1557
02:34:04,314 --> 02:34:05,713
We could settle this right here. . .

1558
02:34:06,874 --> 02:34:08,102
. . .you and me.

1559
02:34:10,034 --> 02:34:11,945
Unfortunately,
it doesn't work that way.

1560
02:34:12,194 --> 02:34:13,866
But it does in your army.

1561
02:34:14,874 --> 02:34:16,785
l invoke Law Seven. . .

1562
02:34:17,434 --> 02:34:18,503
. . .of the Laws of Eight!

1563
02:34:20,474 --> 02:34:24,228
"Any man may challenge
for leadership of the clan" !

1564
02:34:24,474 --> 02:34:25,190
l challenge you.

1565
02:34:25,434 --> 02:34:29,552
You're not a Holnist. You're not
a member. You don't have the right.

1566
02:34:29,794 --> 02:34:31,512
l have every right!

1567
02:34:37,154 --> 02:34:38,507
l invoke Law Seven.

1568
02:34:39,874 --> 02:34:40,750
Where. . .?

1569
02:35:03,154 --> 02:35:04,382
l challenge. . .

1570
02:35:04,634 --> 02:35:06,272
. . .for leadership of the clan!

1571
02:35:06,514 --> 02:35:08,027
Where do l know you from?

1572
02:35:08,794 --> 02:35:10,352
"Cry havoc. . .

1573
02:35:10,674 --> 02:35:12,710
. . .and let slip the dogs of war"

1574
02:35:13,834 --> 02:35:14,903
You remember that?

1575
02:35:17,314 --> 02:35:18,633
Shakespeare.

1576
02:35:19,354 --> 02:35:21,470
The one who didn't want to fight.

1577
02:35:22,114 --> 02:35:25,584
l should have found a way to kill you
then, but you seemed so strong.

1578
02:35:27,234 --> 02:35:28,462
Law Seven. . .

1579
02:35:29,754 --> 02:35:30,823
. . .it is!

1580
02:35:31,874 --> 02:35:33,751
This war is settled here!

1581
02:36:57,274 --> 02:36:58,866
l studied people.

1582
02:37:00,274 --> 02:37:02,105
l know your problem.

1583
02:37:02,754 --> 02:37:03,948
Do you know. . .

1584
02:37:04,194 --> 02:37:06,105
. . .why you can't fight?

1585
02:37:08,234 --> 02:37:11,385
Because you have nothing
to fight for.

1586
02:37:13,914 --> 02:37:15,825
You don't care about anything.

1587
02:37:16,834 --> 02:37:19,428
You don't value anything.

1588
02:37:19,874 --> 02:37:22,434
You don't believe in anything!

1589
02:37:22,674 --> 02:37:24,710
And that's what makes me better.

